# CHANAKYA Radar

- Mission Control default landing — operational intelligence dashboard + Operational Kanban below.
- AI Deal Health / operational quadrants — **not** a lender-stage workflow board.
- Four quadrants: **On Track** (N) · **Follow-up Required** (E) · **At Risk** (S) · **Needs Attention** (W).
- Matrix screen is **retired**. Do not restore Matrix.
- Kanban remains the operational workspace; cards **never** draggable.
- Radar blip hover = tooltip; blip click = Opportunity Preview Panel (right) — do not navigate away.
- Quadrant / KPI click → scroll to Kanban filtered to that category.
- Quadrant labels **outside** the dial; never overlap or touch the visualization; radar resizes dynamically.
- Follow **Enterprise Design & UX Standard v1.0** (`enterprise-screen-ux-standard.mdc`): above-the-fold table/Kanban start, balanced layout, scrollable page, labels outside dial, dynamic radar resize.
- Follow **Data Integrity & Analytics Standard v1.0** (`data-integrity-analytics-standard.mdc`): metrics from LoanFile SSOT, same-session refresh on data change, documented formulas, no demo-as-truth in production.
- Prefer Active Workspace / Opportunity Workspace from Kanban cards and Preview actions.
- Never change Operational Vector / health scoring when adjusting layout chrome.
- Never show Rejected / Lost / Cancelled / Withdrawn / Closed lenders on Radar cards.
